{"title_page": "Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i\n| image          = Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i 20191201.jpg\n| image_size     = 300px\n| caption        = Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i at the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]]\n| fullname       = Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1993|05|15}}\n| height         = 1.94 m\n| birth_place    = [[Di\u1ec5n Ch\u00e2u District|Di\u1ec5n Ch\u00e2u]], [[Ngh\u1ec7 An Province|Ngh\u1ec7 An]], [[Vietnam]]<ref \nname=\"H\u1eadu v\u1ec7 Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i\">{{cite web|title=H\u1eadu v\u1ec7 Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i: C\u1ed1 \u0111\u00e1 b\u00f3ng \u0111\u1ec3 c\u1ee9u gi\u1ea5c m\u01a1 c\u1ee7a anh trai (Defender Que Ngoc Hai: Try to kick the ball for his brother's dream)|url=http://bongdaplus.vn/tin-bai/65/108409/hau-ve-que-ngoc-hai-co-da-bong-de-cuu-giac-mo-cua-anh-trai.bdplus|website=Bong Da Plus|date=1 December 2014|accessdate=16 May 2016|language=Vietnamese|author=Trung Y\u00ean}}</ref>\n| currentclub    = [[Viettel F.C.|Viettel]]\n| clubnumber     = 3\n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = [[S\u00f4ng Lam Ngh\u1ec7 An F.C.|S\u00f4ng Lam Ngh\u1ec7 An]]\n| years1         = 2012\u20132019\n| clubs1         = [[S\u00f4ng Lam Ngh\u1ec7 An F.C.|S\u00f4ng Lam Ngh\u1ec7 An]]\n| caps1          = 119\n| goals1         = 12\n| years2         = 2019\u2013\n| clubs2         = [[Viettel F.C.|Viettel]]\n| caps2          = 21\n| goals2         = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2011\u20132012\n| nationalyears2 = 2014\u20132015\n| nationalyears3 = 2014\u2013\n| nationalteam1  = [[Vietnam national under-20 football team|Vietnam U-19]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 7\n| nationalgoals1 = 2\n| nationalteam2  = [[Vietnam national under-23 football team|Vietnam U-23]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 12\n| nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalteam3  = [[Vietnam national football team|Vietnam]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 46\n| nationalgoals3 = 3\n| pcupdate       = 21 July 2018\n| ntupdate       = 19 November 2019\n}}\n\n'''Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i''' (born 15 May 1993 in  [[Vietnam]]) is a [[Vietnam]]ese [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who is a [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] for [[Th\u1ec3 C\u00f4ng F.C.|Viettel]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] of the [[Vietnam national football team]].\n\nHe scored his first goal for Vietnam in the [[2014 AFF Championship]] in a 2\u20132 draw with [[Indonesia national football team|Indonesia]].<ref name=\"Indonesia\">{{cite web|title=Vietnam 2 Indonesia 2 |url=http://www.affsuzukicup.com/news/vietnam-2-indonesia-2#.VHFOm_nF-So |work=[[ASEAN Football Federation|AFF official website]] |date= 22 November 2014 |accessdate=22 November 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/ngoc-hai--que/231233/ |title=Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i Qu\u1ebf \u2013 Soccerway profile |work=soccerway.com}}</ref>\n\n== Club career ==\n\n=== Tr\u1ea7n Anh Khoa incident ===\nIn a match on 13 September 2015 between [[S\u00f4ng Lam Ngh\u1ec7 An F.C.|S\u00f4ng Lam Ngh\u1ec7 An]] and [[SHB \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng F.C.|SHB \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng]] a player from the latter team, [[Tr\u1ea7n Anh Khoa]], was dribbling into the box at the 21st minute when Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i committed a dangerous and reckless tackle to stop the winger. Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i was only shown a yellow card by the referee but Anh Khoa had to be substituted and suffered serious injury to his knee ligaments and leg bone because of the tackle.<ref>{{cite web|title=C\u1ea7u th\u1ee7 \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng ng\u1ed3i xe l\u0103n sau tr\u1eadn \u0111\u1ea5u SLNA (Da Nang player in wheelchair after the match with SLNA)|url=http://thethao.vnexpress.net/tin-tuc/hau-truong/cau-thu-da-nang-ngoi-xe-lan-sau-tran-dau-slna-3279567.html|publisher=VN Express|date=15 September 2015|accessdate=16 May 2016|language=Vietnamese}}</ref> Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i was later suspended for 6 months for all football-related activities, and was ordered to pay the roughly 800 million [[Vietnamese \u0111\u1ed3ng|\u0111\u1ed3ng]] for Anh Khoa's medical expenses. Anh Khoa is expected to remain injured for 12 to 18 months and had to travel to [[Singapore]] for surgery. Doctors said that there was only a 50% chance of Anh Khoa recovering enough to play professional football again.<ref>{{cite web|title=Anh Khoa ngh\u1ec9 m\u1ed9t n\u0103m, ch\u1ec9 c\u00f3 50% c\u01a1 h\u1ed9i tr\u1edf l\u1ea1i s\u00e2n c\u1ecf (Anh Khoa out for a year, only 50% chance to return to the pitch)|url=http://thethao.vnexpress.net/tin-tuc/hau-truong/anh-khoa-nghi-mot-nam-chi-co-50-co-hoi-tro-lai-san-co-3293013.html|publisher=VN Express|date=9 October 2015|accessdate=16 May 2016|language=Vietnamese}}</ref>\n\nFinally, this incident ends Anh Khoa's football career, his leg never recovers well enough to play football again.\n\n== International career ==\n{{updated|19 November 2019}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! colspan=3 | [[Vietnam national football team|Vietnam]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2014||7||1\n|-\n|2015||3||0\n|-\n|2016||11||0\n|-\n|2017||3||0\n|-\n|2018||10||0\n|-\n|2019||12||2\n|-\n!Total!!46!!3\n|}\n=== International goals ===\n===U-23===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n|1. || 7 June 2015|| [[Bishan, Singapore|Bishan]], [[Bishan Stadium]] || {{fb|Timor-Leste}} || '''3'''\u20130 || 4-0 || [[2015 Southeast Asian Games]]\n|-\n|2. || 15 June 2015|| [[Kallang]], [[National Stadium, Singapore|National Stadium]] || {{fb|Indonesia}} || '''5'''\u20130 || 5-0 || [[2015 Southeast Asian Games]]\n|}\n\n===Vietnam===\n:''Scores and results list Vietnam's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"NFT\">{{NFT player|id=57175|accessdate=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! No. !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition \n|-\n| 1. || 22 November 2014 || [[M\u1ef9 \u0110\u00ecnh National Stadium]], [[Hanoi]] || {{fb|IDN}} || <center>'''1'''\u20130</center> || <center>2\u20132</center> || [[2014 AFF Championship]]\n|-\n| 2. || 16 January 2019 || [[Hazza bin Zayed Stadium]], [[United Arab Emirates]] || {{fb|YEM}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20130 || align=center | 2\u20130 || [[2019 AFC Asian Cup Group D|2019 AFC Asian Cup]]\n|-\n| 3. || 15 October 2019 ||[[Kapten I Wayan Dipta Stadium]], [[Gianyar Regency|Gianyar]], [[Indonesia]]|| {{fb|IDN}} ||align=center | '''2'''\u20130|| align=center | 3\u20131 ||[[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 AFC Second Round#Group G|2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Personal life==\nNg\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i was born in [[Di\u1ec5n Ch\u00e2u District]]. At an early age his family moved to [[Vinh]] because of economical difficulties, where his parents made a living as fruit sellers. Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i and his older brother [[Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc M\u1ea1nh|Ng\u1ecdc M\u1ea1nh]] are very close and attended the [[S\u00f4ng Lam Ngh\u1ec7 An F.C.|S\u00f4ng Lam Ngh\u1ec7 An football academy]] together. Ng\u1ecdc M\u1ea1nh suffered a serious knee injury however, and with little money the family had to rely on Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i to work hard and become professional, both to provide for his family and pay for his brothers surgery.<ref name=\"H\u1eadu v\u1ec7 Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i\"/>\n\nAfter scoring the opening goal against Indonesia in the [[2014 AFF Suzuki Cup]] Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i lifted his shirt to reveal a picture of [[Nguy\u1ec5n H\u1eefu Th\u1eafng (footballer, born 1972)|Nguy\u1ec5n H\u1eefu Th\u1eafng]] to thank his former coach for the opportunities he gave him.<ref name=\"H\u1eadu v\u1ec7 Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i\"/>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===International===\n'''[[Vietnam national football team|Vietnam]]'''\n*'''[[AFF Championship]]''': \n:{{Gold1}} '''Winners :'''  [[2018 AFF Championship|2018]]\n'''[[Vietnam national under-23 football team|Vietnam U23]]'''\n:{{Bronze3}} '''Third place :''' [[Southeast Asian Games]]: [[Football at the 2015 Southeast Asian Games|2015]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{NFT player|pid=57175}}\n\n{{Vietnam squad 2019 AFC Asian Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Que, Ngoc Hai}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Vietnamese footballers]]\n[[Category:Vietnam international footballers]]\n[[Category:People from Ngh\u1ec7 An Province]]\n[[Category:Song Lam Nghe An F.C. players]]\n[[Category:V.League 1 players]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2014 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:2019 AFC Asian Cup players]]\n[[Category:Southeast Asian Games bronze medalists for Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Southeast Asian Games medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2015 Southeast Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Asian Games competitors for Vietnam]]\n\n\n{{Vietnam-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i\n| image          = Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i 20191201.jpg\n| image_size     = 300px\n| caption        = Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i at the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]]\n| fullname       = Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1993|05|15}}\n| height         = 1.83 m\n| birth_place    = [[Di\u1ec5n Ch\u00e2u District|Di\u1ec5n Ch\u00e2u]], [[Ngh\u1ec7 An Province|Ngh\u1ec7 An]], [[Vietnam]]<ref \nname=\"H\u1eadu v\u1ec7 Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i\">{{cite web|title=H\u1eadu v\u1ec7 Qu\u1ebf Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i: C\u1ed1 \u0111\u00e1 b\u00f3ng \u0111\u1ec3 c\u1ee9u gi\u1ea5c m\u01a1 c\u1ee7a anh trai (Defender Que Ngoc Hai: Try to kick the ball for his brother's dream)|url=http://bongdaplus.vn/tin-bai/65/108409/hau-ve-que-ngoc-hai-co-da-bong-de-cuu-giac-mo-cua-anh-trai.bdplus|website=Bong Da Plus|date=1 December 2014|accessdate=16 May 2016|language=Vietnamese|author=Trung Y\u00ean}}</ref>\n| currentclub    = [[Viettel F