 between [[S\u00f4ng Lam Ngh\u1ec7 An F.C.|S\u00f4ng Lam Ngh\u1ec7 An]] and [[SHB \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng F.C.|SHB \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng]] a player from the latter team, [[Tr\u1ea7n Anh Khoa]], was dribbling into the box at the 21st minute when Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i committed a dangerous and reckless tackle to stop the winger. Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i was only shown a yellow card by the referee but Anh Khoa had to be substituted and suffered serious injury to his knee ligaments and leg bone because of the tackle.<ref>{{cite web|title=C\u1ea7u th\u1ee7 \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng ng\u1ed3i xe l\u0103n sau tr\u1eadn \u0111\u1ea5u SLNA (Da Nang player in wheelchair after the match with SLNA)|url=http://thethao.vnexpress.net/tin-tuc/hau-truong/cau-thu-da-nang-ngoi-xe-lan-sau-tran-dau-slna-3279567.html|publisher=VN Express|date=15 September 2015|accessdate=16 May 2016|language=Vietnamese}}</ref> Ng\u1ecdc H\u1ea3i was later suspended for 6 months for all football-related activities, and was ordered to pay the roughly 800 million [[Vietnamese \u0111\u1ed3ng|\u0111\u1ed3ng]] for Anh Khoa's medical expenses. Anh Khoa is expected to remain injured for 12 to 18 months and had to travel to [[Singapore]] for surgery. Doctors said that there was only a 50% chance of Anh Khoa recovering enough to play professional football again.<ref>{{cite web|title=Anh Khoa ngh\u1ec9 m\u1ed9t n\u0103m, ch\u1ec9 c\u00f3 50% c\u01a1 h\u1ed9i tr\u1edf l\u1ea1i s\u00e2n c\u1ecf (Anh Khoa out for a year, only 50% chance to return to the pitch)|url=http://thethao.vnexpress.net/tin-tuc/hau-truong/anh-khoa-nghi-mot-nam-chi-co-50-co-hoi-tro-lai-san-co-3293013.html|publisher=VN Express|date=9 October 2015|accessdate=16 May 2016|language=Vietnamese}}</ref>\n\nFinally, this incident ends Anh Khoa's football career, his leg never recovers well enough to play football again.\n\n== International career ==\n{{updated|19 November 2019}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! colspan=3 | [[Vietnam national foo